description._content: Description: At the Shatt-al-Arab bar_The "British Colonel" at anchor with the ""British Commander"" going alongside to complete the ""British Colonel's"" cargo. Description: View aft from the Captain's deck of the "British Colonel." Captain Kent, the Master, is seen standing in front of the mast beside one of the passengers. Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/714 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown. We have attempted to provide place information for the images automatically but our software may not have found the correct location. For high quality reproductions of any item from our collection please contact our image library
